According to http://googlewebmastercentral.blogspot.com/2009/09/google-does-not-use-keywords-meta-tag.html :
the 'keyword' tag is no longer indexed by google.  We should change this meta tag name from keywords to something that google will actually index (answers_tags?)

This change needs to be made in /forum/skins/atlassian/templates/base_content.html:  
{code}      
<meta name="keywords" content="{% block metakeywords %}{{ settings.APP_KEYWORDS }}{% endblock %}">
